# <%@meta name="title"%>

This report benchmark the performance of <%=colname%>() and <%=rowname%>() against alternative methods.

## Alternative methods

* apply() + diff()
* diff()

## Data
```r
<%=withCapture({
<%@include file="R/random-matrices.R"%>
data <- rmatrices(mode="double")
})%>
```

## Results

<% for (dataLabel in names(data)) { %>
<% message(dataLabel) %>
### <%=dataLabel%> matrix


```r
<%=withCapture({
X <- data[[.dataLabel.]]
gc()

colStats <- microbenchmark(
 colDiffs     = colDiffs(X, na.rm=FALSE),
 "apply+diff" = apply(X, MARGIN=2L, FUN=diff, na.rm=FALSE),
 diff         = diff(X, na.rm=FALSE),
 unit = "ms"
)

X <- t(X)
gc()

rowStats <- microbenchmark(
 rowDiffs     = rowDiffs(X, na.rm=FALSE),
 "apply+diff" = apply(X, MARGIN=1L, FUN=diff, na.rm=FALSE),
 "diff + t"   = diff(t(X), na.rm=FALSE),
 unit = "ms"
)
})%>
```

<% crBenchmarkResults(colStats, rowStats, tags=dataLabel) %>

<% } # for (dataLabel ...) %>


